        <h1> The Bodhi Guide to Moksha<br />
          Settings</h1>
        <hr />
        <p><strong>Moksha Settings</strong> in <strong>Bodhi Linux</strong> can
          be accessed via the <strong>Settings Panel</strong> at <em>Main Menu
            -&gt; Settings -&gt; Settings Panel</em>. </p>
        <p>Note some settings options are only available when certain <a href="modules.html">Modules</a>
          are loaded. </p>
        <table cellpadding="5" border="1">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <h2>Setting</h2>
              </td>
              <td>
                <h2>Description</h2>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td rowspan="1" colspan="2">
                <h3>Look</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Wallpaper</td>
              <td>Change wallpaper or background color</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Application Theme</td>
              <td>Select which theme GTK applications use and icon sets that
                applications use</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Theme</td>
              <td>Select which theme to use</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Colors</td>
              <td>Change theme colors where the theme allows for this</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Fonts</td>
              <td>Choose the font used byÂ  Moksha</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Borders</td>
              <td>Choose border style</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Transitions</td>
              <td>Change window transition settings</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Scaling</td>
              <td>Change scaling factors</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Startup</td>
              <td>Select startup settings including splash screen options</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Apps</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Personal Application Launchers</td>
              <td>GUI for creating .desktop files which can be added to the Main
                Menu.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span style="color: #0000ee;"></span>Favorite Applications</td>
              <td>Add/Remove entries to the Favorites menu. Also allows changing
                order of appearance.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> IBar Applications </td>
              <td> Add/Remove applications to the IBar Gadget. Also allows
                changing the order of appearance.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Screen Lock Applications</td>
              <td>Lock application screens so that they will be as they we left
                after logging out and back in again.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Screen Unlock Applications</td>
              <td>Undo the above.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Restart Applications </td>
              <td> Select applications to automatically run after restarting
                Moksha.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Startup Applications </td>
              <td> Select applications to automatically run at startup.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Default Applications</td>
              <td>Choose which application opens by default given a file type. </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Desktop Environments</td>
              <td>Select which services to use at startup (X11, KDE, Gnome etc)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Screen</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Virtual Desktops</td>
              <td>Adjust the number and layout of Virtual Desktops as well as
                the animation when flipping between them.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Screen Resolution </td>
              <td> Set the screen resolution.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Screen Lock </td>
              <td> Set screen lock time as well as login box location,
                wallpaper, etc.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Blanking</td>
              <td> Enable/Disable X Screensaver, set timer settings, etc.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Backlight</td>
              <td>Set backlight settings (brightness etc).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Windows</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Window Display </td>
              <td> Set window display behavior including moving, resizing, new
                windows, and shading.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Window Focus </td>
              <td> Adjust how mouse interaction changes window focus. Advanced
                options available.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Window Geometry </td>
              <td> Adjust window resistance to elements on the screen and
                parameters when moving/resizing windows via the keyboard.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Window List Menu</td>
              <td> Sets behavior of Window List. Typically accessed by pressing
                <em>Alt+Tab</em></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Window Remembers </td>
              <td> Automatically use most recent window settings for internal
                dialog or file manager windows next time they are opened. Can
                remember all or a subset of window settings including size,
                position, locks, and more. This dialog is primarily to delete
                window remembers. Window remembers are set using the window
                menu.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Window Process Management </td>
              <td>Manage settings to do with how to deal with processes that are
                not responding, such as ping intervals and kill timeout etc</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Window Switcher</td>
              <td>Switch Windows<br />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Menus</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Menu Settings</td>
              <td>Main Menu settings. Adjust what application info is displayed
                as well as menu scrolling behavior.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Configuration Panel</td>
              <td>Show configurations in Menu</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Language</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Desklock Language Settings</td>
              <td>Lock language settings</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Language Settings </td>
              <td> Set the locale settings for the environment.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Input Method Settings </td>
              <td> Adjust settings for various Input Methods which allow users
                to input symbols not found on their input device. E.g. entering
                Chinese characters with a Latin keyboard.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Files</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Placesclose</td>
              <td> Adjust settings for Places module. Allows access to file
                manager via Main Menu as well as using a custom file manager </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Advanced</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Signal Bindings</td>
              <td>Set system signals to actions - ie mouse click/Lid Closed etc</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Syscon</td>
              <td>Change settings to do with shutting down etc</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Performance</td>
              <td>Settings to change caching frequency and other functions that
                affect performance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Engine</td>
              <td>Border graphics settings</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Power Management</td>
              <td>Settings to do with power management (restart etc)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Search Directories</td>
              <td><br />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Battery Meter</td>
              <td><br />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Environment Variables</td>
              <td><br />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Look</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Wallpaper </td>
              <td> Change the wallpaper for all desktops or current desktop.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Wallpaper 2 </td>
              <td> A fancier dialog for changing wallpaper for all desktops or
                current desktop.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="themes.html">Theme</a></td>
              <td>Switch Enlightenment themes. Advanced options allow assigning
                Themes to individual elements.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Colors </td>
              <td> Assign custom colors to individual Enlightenment elements.
                Colors depend on Theme capabilities.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Fonts </td>
              <td> Assign custom font preferences for Enlightenment. Advanced
                options allow assigning customizations to individual elements.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Borders </td>
              <td> Set default window border style.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Icon Theme </td>
              <td> Set the Icon theme to use throughout Enlightenment.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Mouse Cursor </td>
              <td> Choose between X or Enlightenment style mouse pointer as well
                as set the size.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Transitions </td>
              <td> Set the type of transition to use for certain events e.g.
                changing the background.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Scaling </td>
              <td> Scale the overall font settings throughout Enlightenment.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Startup </td>
              <td> Set the splash screen animation to use at boot-up.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Composite Scale Windows </td>
              <td> Set animation settings for the scale windows action. Scale
                Windows is an alternative way of navigating between open
                windows.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="compositing.html">Composite</a></td>
              <td>Set Composite Module effects and tune Composite performance.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="2">
                <h3>Input</h3>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="key_bindings.html">Keys</a></td>
              <td>Key Bindings (Keyboard shortcuts) settings.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td> Edge Bindings </td>
              <td> Similar to Key Bindings. Set actions to occur when using the
